  						<table border='0' cellpadding='3' cellspacing='0' width='92%'>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' align='center'>SWIFTTAIL, THE TALE OF SLEAT, CHAPTER 5</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%'><font face='verdana' size='2pt'><P>Sleat meditates, his body heals the bruises along his back and shoulders from the day’s lessons slowly heal. He feels a power overwhelm his body, he smiles hmmmmmm master Arvel is close, his scales slide along his back his whole body itches at the feel of the masters power, he drifts back many years he is a young Swifttail the training ground sand was burning hot and scalding his back, his locked arm was held stiff in Master Brea’s grip she hisses her lessons so all can hear he feels the joint of his elbow flex as she puts more pressure against his forearm his body quivers as pain lances thru his body, Master Brea smiles at him he is her favorite student to show the others the daily lessons this young Sleat thrives on pain his body reacts with such wonderful pleasure with  each strike or throw, no matter how much she uses him he never once has shown fear or hesitated , he will make a fine Swifttail.</p>

<p>Sleat stands and shakes the hot sand off his body his arm and shoulder burn with pain, he shivers with pleasure he walks back to his place and stands while Master Brea scold a older Swifttail he shrinks back and cowers causing her rage to build to show fear is a mortal sin to Master Brea.</p>

<p>He breathes in and calms himself, willing his two hearts to slow he breaths in and out slowly. Sleat hisses as a shadow passes overhead, he turns and snorts in disbelief as a human land in the middle of the arena, Master Brea spins dropping the cringing student,
Sleat sees her talons slip from their protective sheaths on each finger, she hisses at the human, Sleat feels his hearts beat as the human speaks in perfect lizard man, Hail mighty Swifttails I have come on request of master Lea, the human laughs I was told all I have to do is earn master Lea’s respect and I will be welcome into the Swifttails clan. Sleat feels his body shiver as master lea shrieks at the human her fighting lids snapping down over her eyes.
Brea advances and the young Swifttails leave the training grounds they crouch in small groups watching the duel with intense interest.</p>

<p>Sleat sees Grand Master lea enter the training grounds, he crouches down and watches. Sleat studies the human he is far different from all the other humans he has ever seen in the city, this one is not stooped and broken from years of labor and abuse, Sleat watches as he moves, this human glides across the sand with each step, Sleat has heard of human monks of great power and skill, Brea attacks with blinding speed her talons out stretched to rip this humans face from his body her claws slice thru air the human kicks her in the tail sending her sprawling to the ground Sleat suppresses a hiss never has he seen Master Brea miss let alone be hit , she recovers quickly brushing the sand from the arena off her robe she bows  to master Lea so grand master she hisses in laughter  you have finally  found me a worthy opponent after all these years, she reaches to her shoulder and lets the robe drop away from her body Sleat hisses at the amount of scars that cover her body his hand goes to his one scare above his twin hearts</p>

 <p>she steps forward and bows to the human clasping her arms across her chest I am Master Brea human I accept your challenge, will this be to the death or to the first fall, the human made a loud noise that Sleat later learned is a human laugh if we where to fight to the first fall master Brea I would have won already, he smiles, let us fight until the other cannot fight anymore I promises I shall not kill you, if you promises not to loose your self in rage again and give me such an easy target as before, Sleat sees Master Brea shoulders stiffen  in shame, she bows to the human  I accept  your change human I will  not kill you but if I win you will be my servant until I see fit to release you , the human bows and I will request  as the boon your humble respect  as an equal If I am to best you.,</p>

 <p> I am master Arvel of the thunder fists, I have come in search of my old friend master Lea, after many years of travel to many far lands I find him here among his own people the Grand Master rises and bows to the human, my long lost friend I will await you in my meditation chambers when this is duel is done, I have no fear as to the outcome of this, he bows to Master Brea I mean you no disrespect my friend, she bows back none taken Grand Master, she looks at the human with new respect.</p>

<p>The fight starts out slowly each one testing the other for weakness suddenly the human stands straight and closes his eyes he shifts into a stance Sleat has never seen and waits, Master Brea looks at this foolish human her head tilts to the side, how will he fight with his eyes closed.</p>
 
<p>She strikes and misses, his blow hits her below her ribs, she chokes as the air forced is from her body with such power she stumbles, she rakes her tail across the humans face slashing a long slice along his cheek, he grunts his eyes still closed, he laughs out loud, I will never get used to those tails, blood drips down his face from the tail rack, Master Brea silently shifts behind the human she kicks out with her foot aiming at his head, he spins and grabs her leg kicking out with his feet and pulling her forward she lands on her back with a grunt . The human steps back, I have learned what I need to know my good opponent he waits for her to stand.</p>
<p> He strikes out with such speed Brea staggers blood flying from her left nostril, her bright yellow facial markings go pale, the human laughs his foot strikes snapping her head back pulling her from her feet she lands on her back with another grunt, the human tells her to rise surly a Swifttail can take more that the few touches he has landed.</p>
<p> Master Brea jumps to her feet her lower lips split and bleeding Sleat sees a couple teeth are missing from her mouth, she strikes at the human he steps away and she stumbles he grabs her arm and twists putting her into the position Sleat was in earlier today, he kicks out at him he catches her foot Sleat grimaces as he hears her arm snap from the pressure she put on her arm from the kick, The human stepped back I had not wanted to injure you my good monk he offers a hand to Master Brea she takes it and stands, she bows to the human  I will continue fighting  she states and  crouches into a stance the human shakes his head, I will never understand your kinds unwillingness to bend he strikes with suck speed Sleat never sees the blow he feels the air around master Brea compress and she falls to the ground he eyes rolled back into her head, the human watches as she hits the ground and looks at Sleat he cocks his head then smiles go get a shaman to heal your Master boy, Sleat jumps up and runs from the training arena to do this strange Masters bidding .</P>
<P>Later that night at the common feeding area Grand Master Lea enters the ground all heads go down in respect he tells them to raise there heads in honor as master Brea enters the room her wounds healed, behind her came the human a simple robe covered his body.</P>

<P>Grand Master Leas hand snaps to his chest with a loud slap, all the students hands followed suit, may I introduce a long lost friend and now member of the Swifttails until others call him away Master Arvel, the human steps forward. Sleat feels the raw power radiate from his body it flows over the crowed, he quickly shuts it off in respect for the Grand master, all heads lower Master Brea never stood a chance.</P>

<P>After the meal Sleat was summoned to the grand Masters hut, Sleat entered the hut on his knees his neck exposed, he hears the voice of the human deep in the hut, the grand master tells Sleat to rise and come sit near the fire, as Sleat crouched by the fire he listens to the grand master talk of his brood father Mir, to the human, the human turns to Sleat and lays a hand on his shoulder, I knew you looked familiar my young Iskar, I also knew your father he gave me this the human pointed to his neck a large scar ran across his neck from shoulder to chin , the human laughed, when I was much younger my mouth was bigger than my skill, yet your brood sire took pity on me and spared my life in return I became his student  while he traveled among my people, he winked at Sleat grand master Lea and I where his students, I have come to teach  the Swiftails all I know in honor of  the great Mir .</p>
 
<p>Master Arvel trained them in the human style of combat more kicks than he knew where possible, new strikes and many new stances where his to learn Sleat soaked up all the lessons like a Sponge his hunger for Knowledge and training never lessened he would train for hour often being forced to sleep by his masters</p>
<p> Sleat grew slowly at first as all Iskar's do, then the change came upon his body his bones grew in spurts, painful spurts sometimes it would be days before he could walk, then came the skull spikes six in all they broke from the hard leathery ridge on his head all at once forming a hard bony ridge Sleat thought he was going to die the mixture of pain and pleasure was so intense, he could hardly pay attention to anything, he earned a lot of beatings from master Brea for his lack of attention.</p>

<p>Sleat opens his eyes as master Arvel approaches, he stood in front of Sleat his arms folded in his simple robes master Brea stands behind him she holds two packs, master Arvel bows to Sleat as he rises to his full 6 foot 6 height Sleat looks down at the master and bows back. 
Master Arvel clears his throat I have been called back my son I must return to the lands of humans, he looks back I have accepted master Brea’s company as my student until she is ready to strike out as a true master she will walk in my foot steps training human and Iskar alike until she someday will take a young student to train as I have. It has been this way for eons and will always be this way.</p>

 <p>I have also been told your time is here my son, he tosses Sleat a small sack, you must avenge Grand master Gloxs death, the time is here you are ready, I give you theses gifts to help you with your task it will not be easy my son, but it is necessary. It is not just fate that you will be the executioner of this sentence, Grand Master Glox was your brood fathers teacher, you will never hear that from any of the masters here but we humans think differently, we grow attached to each other, I loved your brood father as a teacher and a master, and I know Mir cared for Grand Master Glox.</p>

<p>You will not fail Sleat of the Swifttail clan, you are destined for many things in this life I have seen many visions in my meditations; we will meet again my son. Sleat stood and watched the human walk away master Brea following behind him, Sleat lowers his head a strange feeling forms in his throat it burns and makes him have pain, this pain gives him no pleasure it is just pain.</p>

<p>Sleat takes the small bag to his small hut in the monk compound. He meditates. He will soon have to kill the warrior guild master, 
He will not fail, for master Glox and the strange human master Arvel he will not fail………………………………….</p>
 </font></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%'><small>By <b>Lyrak</b> Submited on 11/19/2001</small></td>
